From: Andre Przywara <andre.przywara@arm.com>
Date: Fri, 11 May 2018 15:20:14 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] KVM: arm/arm64: VGIC/ITS: protect kvm_read_guest() calls with
 SRCU lock
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.16.11
Git-commit: bf308242ab98b5d1648c3663e753556bef9bec01

commit bf308242ab98b5d1648c3663e753556bef9bec01 upstream.

kvm_read_guest() will eventually look up in kvm_memslots(), which requires
either to hold the kvm->slots_lock or to be inside a kvm->srcu critical
section.
In contrast to x86 and s390 we don't take the SRCU lock on every guest
exit, so we have to do it individually for each kvm_read_guest() call.

Provide a wrapper which does that and use that everywhere.

Note that ending the SRCU critical section before returning from the
kvm_read_guest() wrapper is safe, because the data has been *copied*, so
we don't need to rely on valid references to the memslot anymore.

